Cloud Provider Selection

ProtectWave VPN will use Amazon Web Services (AWS) as the cloud provider.

Reasons for choosing AWS:

Global availability
High reliability and uptime
Strong security standards
Easy scalability for future growth
Industry-standard choice for VPN services
AWS allows us to deploy VPN servers in multiple countries using its global infrastructure.

Region Selection

For the initial launch, ProtectWave VPN will start with three server locations as required:
Server Location	AWS Region Code
United Kingdom	eu-west-2
Germany	eu-central-1
Portugal	eu-west-3

Business & User Benefits

Users can select the country they want to connect to
Better speed due to geographic proximity
Improved reliability and redundancy
Global presence from day one

Usage in Application

When a user selects a country in the app:
The VPN client connects to the corresponding AWS server running WireGuard in that region.

Future Expansion

More regions and servers can be added easily using AWS infrastructure as the user base grows.

Summary

Cloud Provider: AWS
Initial Regions: UK, Germany, Portugal
Purpose: Secure, fast, and globally accessible VPN service
